tags.name: North Diamond
tags.note: The North Diamond is the oldest diamond at the park.  It is primarily used for Pony League or Babe Ruth League games, however it will also be used for tournament games in other leagues.  The best place to park is the parking lot off County Rd M.

tags.name: South Diamond
tags.note: The South Diamond is the least used field in the park.  It is used for High School aged kids and the various leagues that they play in.  The South Diamonds elevation is much lower than that of the other diamonds so it tends to flood.

tags.name: West Diamond
tags.note: The West and East Diamonds are used primarily for Little League and Tee Ball.  The fields are up-kept nicely and there is a variety of seating ranging from bleachers to picnic    tables.  It is best to park in the parking lot off John St.

tags.name: East Diamond
tags.note: The West and East Diamonds are used primarily for Little League and Tee Ball.  The fields are up-kept nicely and there is a variety of seating ranging from bleachers to picnic    tables.  It is best to park in the parking lot off John St.

tags.name: Miller Park Ball Diamond
tags.note: For everything from Tee Ball Practice to Beer Softball Leagues, Miller Park is your place to go.  With no fences or bleachers, Miller Park is the perfect backyard ball diamond.

tags.name: Tennis Courts
tags.note: If you're looking to play some tennis in Hortonville, this is the only place to go.  If you have a couple of rackets, a ball, and a friend, this is a perfect way to spend a lazy Saturday afternoon.

tags.description: Lutz Park was established in 1925 when Lawrence Lutz donated 2.7 acres of land along the Fox River to the city of Appleton.
tags.name: Lutz Park

tags.description: Grills, picnic tables, playground, basketball half-court, softball/little league diamond (fenced and lighted with bleachers), volleyball court soccer field (with bleachers), roller hockey rink tennis court (lighted), off-street parking (80 vehicles).
